THOUGHT: The crash indicates an insertelement does not dominate a shufflevector use. In SLP’s CreateInsertElement lambda, insertelement can be emitted in a block that doesn’t dominate the later shuffle. To fix dominance, I’ll hoist insertelement when both the scalar and the current vector operand are non-instructions (e.g., argument/constant and poison), by temporarily setting the IRBuilder insertion point to the function entry block before creating the insertelement, guarded with IRBuilderBase::InsertPointGuard. This avoids hoisting when the vector operand depends on an instruction (which might not be available at entry). Then I’ll build and run submit-patch.

```bash
sed -i '/Vec = Builder.CreateInsertElement(Vec, Scalar, Builder.getInt32(Pos));/i \      IRBuilderBase::InsertPointGuard Guard(Builder);
      if (!isa<Instruction>(Scalar) && !isa<Instruction>(Vec)) {
        if (BasicBlock *InsertBB = Builder.GetInsertBlock()) {
          if (Function *F = InsertBB->getParent()) {
            auto FI = F->getEntryBlock().getFirstInsertionPt();
            if (FI != F->getEntryBlock().end())
              Builder.SetInsertPoint(&*FI);
          }
        }
      }' llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp && submit-patch
```

