- Remove the earlier pointer hoist block in CreateInsertElement (to restore original ordering).
- Update ShuffleIRBuilder::createShuffleVector (both overloads) to, just before creating the shuffle, replace any operand insertelement that doesn’t dominate the IP (or appears later in the same block) with a freshly built insertelement at the IP using a poison base and same scalar/index.
